page.title: 19MOTHS AND BUTTERFLIES
page.content: Over 100 different types of moth have been caught in a light-trap placed in a garden in the village of Merton.They include the garden tiger moth,herald moth,lackey moth and angleshades moth. These are common and breed in gardens and hedgerows. There are twenty types of butterflies living in this area, most are found on roadsides, riverbanks, and in the gardens. Three more species, the red admiral, painted lady, the clouded yellow, migrate into the area most years. The most common butterflies are the orange-tip; the large, small and green-veined whites; small tortoishell; peacock; meadow brown; hedge brown; and large skipper.
